COS314 Assignment 2 — Knapsack Solver
======================================

## Project Structure

  YourProject/
  ├── src/
  │   ├── Main.java
  │   ├── KnapsackInstance.java
  │   ├── IteratedLocalSearch.java
  │   └── GeneticAlgorithm.java     <- stub, not yet implemented
  ├── data/                         <- your Knapsack Instances folder goes here
  │   ├── f1_l-d_kp_10_269
  │   ├── f2_l-d_kp_20_878
  │   ├── f3_l-d_kp_4_20
  │   ├── f4_l-d_kp_4_11
  │   ├── f5_l-d_kp_15_375
  │   ├── f6_l-d_kp_10_60
  │   ├── f7_l-d_kp_7_50
  │   ├── knapPI_1_100_1000_1
  │   ├── f8_l-d_kp_23_10000
  │   ├── f9_l-d_kp_5_80
  │   └── f10_l-d_kp_20_879
  └── KnapsackSolver.jar

IMPORTANT: The "data" folder must be in the same directory as the JAR
           when you run it — NOT inside src.

## Compiling (from the project root)

  javac -d out src/*.java
  jar cfe KnapsackSolver.jar Main -C out .

## Running

  java -jar KnapsackSolver.jar

When prompted, enter an integer seed value (e.g. 42).

## Output

A table is printed showing for each of the 10 instances:
  - Problem instance filename
  - Algorithm (ILS / GA)
  - Best solution value found
  - Known optimum (for reference only — not used by the algorithms)
  - Runtime in seconds

## Algorithm — Iterated Local Search (ILS)

  1. Generate greedy initial solution (items sorted by value/weight ratio)
  2. Improve with bit-flip hill climbing (local search)
  3. For 1000 iterations:
       a. Perturb: flip 3 random bits
       b. Local search on perturbed solution
       c. Accept if >= current fitness (greedy acceptance)
       d. Track global best

## Status

  ILS  — fully implemented
  GA   — stub only (returns 0), to be implemented